Conditional Statements:
    1.      if,else
    2.      else if
    3.      ternary operator
    4.      switch

3.  Ternary Operator:
        ->  variable = condition? statement1 : statement2;
        ->  e.g.,
                bool isAdult = (age >= 18)? true : false;

4.  Switch Statement:
        e.g., switch(day){
            case 1: cout<<"Monday";
                    break;
            case 2: cout<<"Tuesday";
                    break;
            default: cout<<"Invalid";
        }